            "title": "Fintech in Islamic finance : theory and practice",
            "abstract": [
                "Featuring high-level analysis of Islamic law, this book examines fintech in Islamic finance from both theoretical and empirical perspectives. Whilst building on existing approaches, it also discusses the current application of fintech in promoting financial inclusion within Shariah law, identifing future directions for policy-makers. With original chapters written by prominent academics, senior lawyers and practitioners in the global Islamic finance industry, this book serves as the first standalone pioneering reference work on fintech in Islamic finance. It also, for the first time, examines the position of Islamic law on cryptocurrencies, such as bitcoin. Besides the conceptual analysis of the Shar\u012bah and legal aspects of Islamic finance, this book provides relevant case studies showing current and potential developments in the application of fintech in various sectors ranging from crowdfunding and smart contracts, to Online Dispute Resolution, Investment Account Platform and identity verification in the KYC process. Setting the agenda for researchers in the field, Fintech in Islamic Finance will be useful to students and scholars of Islamic finance and finance technology",
                "Fintech in Islamic finance : an introduction / Umar A. Oseni, S. Nazim Ali -- Fintech and financial intermediation -- Fintech : the opportunity for Islamic finance / Harris Irfan, Daniel Ahmed -- Implications of technological advance for financial intermediation in Islamic finance / Rodney Wilson -- Fintech in Islamic finance : from collaborative finance to community-based finance / Celia de Anca -- Financial intermediation, fintech and shari'ah compliance / Shariq Nisar, Umar Farooq -- E-commerce and Islamic financial intermediation / Hafis Bello -- Setting the shari'ah paramters -- Fintech in the light of Maqasid al-shari'ah / Mustafa Omar Mohammed, Mohamed Cherif el Amri -- Fintech and Islamic finance : setting the shari'ah parameters / Mohamad Akram Laldin, Hafas Furqani -- Currency in Islamic law : a shari'ah analysis of bitcoin / Mufti Faraz Adam, Mufti Abdul Kadir Barkatulla -- Crowdfunding in Islamic finance : ensuring proper shari'ah oversight / Muhammad al Bashir M. al-Amine -- Legal and regulatory issues -- The regulation of fintech and cryptocurrencies / Nafis Alam, Abdolhossein Zameni -- Fintech in Islamic finance : business models and the need for legal solutions / Michael Gassner, Jonathan Lawrence -- Blockchain technologies and the prospects of smart contracts in Islamic finance / Volker Nienhaus -- The potentials of smart contract in Islamic trade finance / Leisan Safina, Umar A. Oseni -- Case studies : from concept to application -- The emergence of Islamic crowdfunding platforms : a case study of ethis ventures / Ahmad Sabree, Umar Munshi -- The investment account platform : a practical application of fintech in Malaysia / Noor Suhaida Kasri, Marjan Muhammad -- Integrating waqf crowdfunding into the blockchain : a modern approach for creating a waqf market / Magda Ismail Abdel Mohsin, Aishath Muneeza -- Blockdentity : a future beyond digital identity / Ishaq Mustapha Akinlaso, Ibrahim Opeyemi Adediran, Abdoulaye Kindy Diallo, Ziyaad Mahomed -- Banking on ICT : the relevance of online dispute resolution in the Islamic banking industry in Malaysia / Umar A. Oseni, Sodiq O. Omoola -- Future directions -- Current trends and future impacts of fintech in Islamic finance / Sirajulhaq Yasini, Marifatulhaq Yasini."
